12 An Act relating to definitions; defining family
resource center; providing for codification; and
13 providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 52 of Title 25, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 The term "family resource center" means a community, school, or
21 faith-based hub of support services for families that:
22 1. Utilizes an approach that is multigenerational, strengths-
23 based, and family-centered;
24
HB4117 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. Reflects, and is responsive to, community needs and
2 interests;
3 3. Provides support at no or low cost for participants;
4 4. Builds communities of peer support for families, including
5 kinship families, to develop social connections that reduce
6 isolation and stress; and
7 5. Integrates access to supportive employment services that
8 build skills, strengthen workforce attachment, and promote long-term
9 family stability.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
11
